HEADWORD: Service hat
<hw>Serv"ice hat</hw> }</mhw>.
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A cap or hat worn by officers or enlisted men
when full-dress uniform, or dress uniform, is not worn.</def> <note>In
the United States army the <ex>service cap</ex> is round, about
3⟦frac12⟧ inches high, flat-topped, with a visor. The <ex>service
hat</ex> is of soft felt of khaki color, with broad brim and high crown,
creased down the middle.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Service elevator</ent>⟦br⟧
